by vudaltsov at 2019-02-04T12:10:08Z

@OskarStark , it's okay. If you have `null` as a default value that means that the argument is nullable. Otherwise how it might have `null` as a default? See the accepted RFC https://wiki.php.net/rfc/nullable_types#default_values

